<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 12:43AM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Montague County
through 115 AM CDT...
At 1243 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bowie, moving east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bowie, Nocona, St. Jo, Lake Nocona, Sunset, Lake Amon G Carter,
Nocona Hills, Montague, Fruitland, Capps Corner, Forestburg,
Ringgold, Spanish Fort, Stoneburg, Belcherville, Mallard, Bonita and
Illinois Bend.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 600 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
